description:
## Problem
The @dotdo/capnweb package has ZERO unit tests despite being the foundation of all other packages. This is a critical gap for beta quality.

## What Needs Testing

### Error Classes (src/index.ts:309-454)
```typescript
// tests/errors.test.ts
describe('CapnwebError', () => {
  it('should have correct name property', () => {
    const error = new CapnwebError('test');
    expect(error.name).toBe('CapnwebError');
  });

  it('should have correct code property', () => {
    const error = new CapnwebError('test', 'CAPNWEB_ERROR');
    expect(error.code).toBe('CAPNWEB_ERROR');
  });

  it('should support instanceof checks', () => {
    const error = new ConnectionError('test');
    expect(error).toBeInstanceOf(CapnwebError);
    expect(error).toBeInstanceOf(Error);
  });
});

describe('ConnectionError', () => {
  it('should extend CapnwebError');
  it('should have CONNECTION_ERROR code');
});

describe('RpcError', () => {
  it('should extend CapnwebError');
  it('should include methodId in message');
});

describe('TimeoutError', () => {
  it('should extend CapnwebError');
  it('should have TIMEOUT_ERROR code');
});
```

### MessageBuilder (if exists)
```typescript
describe('MessageBuilder', () => {
  it('should build valid call messages');
  it('should build valid return messages');
  it('should build valid abort messages');
});
```

### Type Exports
