## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] 100% of error classes have tests
- [ ] Error prototype chain verified
- [ ] Error codes verified
- [ ] Type exports verified (compile-time)
- [ ] Minimum 20 tests for capnweb package

## Problem
Go capnweb and rpc packages appear to have stub implementations returning ErrNotImplemented.

## RED (Write failing tests)
```go
// capnweb/capnweb_test.go
func TestEncodeMessage(t *testing.T) {
    msg := Message{Type: "call", Method: "test"}
    encoded, err := EncodeMessage(msg)
    if err != nil {
        t.Fatalf("EncodeMessage failed: %v", err)
    }
    if len(encoded) == 0 {
        t.Fatal("EncodeMessage returned empty result")
